environmental.systemBoundary: The system boundaries comprise the cradle-to-gate process for manufacturing steel studs. The final manufacturing step -- the roll forming process for the production of steel stud and track -- takes place in a roll forming facility and includes the following processing steps to create the final product: Uncoiling --> Slitting --> Recoiling --> Roll forming. Upstream data includes steel manufacturing, energy production, and lubricants production, as well as transportation to the roll forming facility. Packaging is excluded.

name: Steel Studs
description: Drywall studs are used as the vertical support in wall framing and are typically made of galvanized steel. They are available in a range of widths, lengths and gauge depending on requirements for strength, height, impact resistance and sound insulation. This Common Product profile represents a metal stud suitable for non-structural wall framing and meets ASTM C 645 (Standard Specification for Nonstructural Steel Framing Members) which also includes a protective hot-dipped galvanized coating of (G40) at minimum. The characterization of the steel used in this product was created in compliance with ASTM A1003 (Sec 4, Paras 4.1-2m, Standard Specification for Steel Sheet, Carbon, Metallic- and Nonmetallic-Coated for Cold-Formed Framing Members)
